Forms in HTML
<body>
    <h1>Form to Apply for the course</h1>
    <form action="post">
        <div>
        <label for="username">User Name:</label>
        <input type="username" id="username" placeholder="type your user name">
        </div>
        <div>
        <label>
            Male
            <input type="radio" '
            name="gender" value="male" />
        </label>
        <label>
            Female
            <input type="radio"
            name="gender" value="female" />
        </label>
        </div>
        <div>
            <input type="checkbox" id="subscribe" name="subscribe" value="yes">
            <label for="subscribe">Subscribe to our newsletter</label> 
        </div>
        <div>
            <label for="comment">enter your comment here</label><br>
            <textarea name="comment" row="4" cols="50"></textarea>
        </div>
        <div>
            <select name="strength">
                <option value="Web Development">Web Development</option>
                <option value="Andoid">Android</option>
                <option value="DSA">DSA</option>
            </select>
        </div>
    </form>
</body>


Learnt about various feature of form in HTML like:
1. input type username
2. input type radio 
3. input type checkbox
4. select feature of the drop down list
5. label for each inpute type
